│   └── layer5_prd.md
└── README.md
```

### Structural Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Supabase migrations numbered serially | Ensures reproducible, ordered schema deployment. Migrations are never edited after merge — only additive. |
| Edge Functions separate per concern | Scoring, pruning, cold-start, trust, and trend are independent cron jobs. Failure of one does not cascade. |
| Hono for API layer | Lightweight, Deno/Node compatible, typed middleware chain — ideal for Supabase Edge deployment. Can swap to Express if self-hosting. |
| Vite + React for dashboard | Fastest dev setup; no SSR needed for internal dashboard. Can be replaced with Next.js if customer-facing later. |
| Tests split by layer | Enables phase-gated validation — Layer 1 tests pass before Layer 2 is built. |
| `context-embed.ts` isolated | Embedding provider (OpenAI, local) swapped without touching scoring logic. |
| `dim_institutional_knowledge` omitted from migrations list | Created as a materialized view derivative in Phase 4 — not a separate migration. |

