## Dependency Map

```
Phase 1 (Schema)
    │
    ├──→ Phase 2 (Materialized Views)
    │         │
    │         └──→ Phase 3 (Scoring API)
    │                   │
    │                   ├──→ Phase 4 (Temporal / Trend)
    │                   │         │
    │                   └──→ Phase 5 (Policy Engine)
    │                                   │
    └───────────────────────────────────└──→ Phase 6 (Trust + Dashboard)
```

**What breaks if you skip or reorder**:

| Skip | Consequence |
|---|---|
| Phase 1 (schema) | Nothing else can exist — no tables, no views, no API |
| Phase 2 (views) | Phase 3 API has no pre-computed scores — every query hits raw `fact_outcomes` (too slow) |
| Phase 3 (API) | Phase 4 and Phase 5 logic has no integration point — untestable |
| Phase 4 (trends) | Phase 5 policy engine has no trend data to factor into explore/exploit decisions |
| Phase 5 (policy) | Phase 6 trust system has no policy context — trust scores exist but cannot route decisions |
| Build Phase 2 first | `REFRESH CONCURRENTLY` fails — no tables exist for the view to query |

