```
□ Supabase account created at supabase.com
□ New Supabase project created (region: closest to Hyderabad = ap-south-1)
□ Project URL saved: SUPABASE_URL=https://[project-ref].supabase.co
□ Anon key saved:    SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=[from Supabase dashboard]
□ Service role key saved (NEVER commit): SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=[from dashboard]

□ Supabase CLI installed: npm install -g supabase
□ CLI authenticated: supabase login
□ CLI linked to project: supabase link --project-ref [project-ref]

□ pgvector extension enabled:
    → Supabase Dashboard → Database → Extensions → Search "vector" → Enable
□ uuid-ossp confirmed active (usually on by default in Supabase PostgreSQL):
    → SELECT * FROM pg_extension WHERE extname = 'uuid-ossp';

□ Git repository initialized: git init
□ .gitignore created (must include: .env, node_modules/, supabase/.branches/)
□ .env.example created (template with all required keys, no real values)
□ Node.js v20+ confirmed: node --version

□ API project bootstrapped: cd api && npm init -y && npm install hono @supabase/supabase-js
□ TypeScript configured: npm install -D typescript tsx @types/node
□ Test runner installed: npm install -D vitest
□ Dashboard project bootstrapped: cd dashboard && npm create vite@latest . -- --template react-ts

□ First migration dry-run: supabase db push --dry-run
    → Expected: no errors on schema validation

□ README.md created with: project overview, setup steps, migration run order, test commands
```

