## Critical Non-Negotiable Rules

| # | Rule | Violation Flag |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `fact_outcomes` is APPEND-ONLY | Any UPDATE on fact_outcomes → STOP. Flag immediately. |
| 2 | UUID everywhere | Any `SERIAL` or `INT` primary key → STOP. Rewrite with `gen_random_uuid()`. |
| 3 | TIMESTAMPTZ everywhere | Any `TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE` → STOP. Replace with `TIMESTAMPTZ`. |
| 4 | CONCURRENTLY for all view refreshes | Any `REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW` without `CONCURRENTLY` → STOP. Requires unique index first. |
| 5 | Indexes before data | Index created after table population = potential hours of downtime on prod. Never. |
| 6 | RLS on all tenant-scoped tables | Any table with `customer_id` missing RLS policy → STOP. |
| 7 | Hallucination prevention mandatory | Any path that writes to `fact_outcomes` before validating `action_name` against `dim_actions` → STOP. |
| 8 | One phase = one git commit | Do not begin next phase until previous phase passes test gate and is committed. `git commit -m "feat: layer-[N] complete"` |

